&reftitle.description;
final public arrayMongoDB\Driver\WriteResult::getErrorReplies
Returns the error reply documents that were returned by the server for the write operation. These complement the individual write errors reported by MongoDB\Driver\WriteResult::getWriteErrors and the write concern error reported by MongoDB\Driver\WriteResult::getWriteConcernError.

&reftitle.returnvalues;

 Returns an array of error reply documents from the server. The array will be
 empty if the server did not report any such error replies.

  &reftitle.examples;

   MongoDB\Driver\WriteResult::getErrorReplies example


<?php

$manager = new MongoDB\Driver\Manager;

$bulk = new MongoDB\Driver\BulkWrite;
$bulk->insert(['_id' => 1]);
$bulk->insert(['_id' => 1]);

try {
    $manager->executeBulkWrite('db.collection', $bulk);
} catch (MongoDB\Driver\Exception\BulkWriteException $e) {
    $result = $e->getWriteResult();

    // Any error reply documents reported by the server
    var_dump($result->getErrorReplies());
}

?>
